## DocumentAttributeSet

* *Attribute types*: `document`, various other types depending on application type
* *Operations*: [documentLayout](#documentLayout)

Contains global document settings, and default attribute values for different attribute types supported by the current application. Default attribute values are used to determine the value of an attribute that is neither specified by a style sheet referenced by a component nor by an explicit attribute of the component.

|Property|Data Type|Default Value|Application|Description|
|--------|---------|-------------|-----------|-----------|
|`document`|[DocumentAttributes](#documentattributes)|{}|all|Global document settings, depending on the document type.|
|`page`|[PageAttributes](#pageattributes)|{}|all|Default page attributes.|
|`defaultTextListStyles`|[TO\_BE\_DEFINED](#to_be_defined)|{}|Presentation|Default text list styles that are used for non presentation objects.|
|`character`|[CharacterAttributes](#characterattributes)|{}|all|Default character attributes for drawing objects, text documents, and spreadsheet cells.|
|`paragraph`|[ParagraphAttributes](#paragraphattributes)|{}|Text|Default paragraph attributes for text documents.|
|`cell`|[CellAttributes](#cellattributes)|{}|Spreadsheet|Default cell attributes for spreadsheet documents.|
|`layout`|[LayoutAttributes](#layoutattributes)|{}|Presentation|Width in percent from the slide pane for presentation documents.|

